notes:
I had similar success after getting the WMV supported. No issues so far. I did not go through the multiple steps to install WMP10. I used the following basic steps using the x64 version of WMP11 for Windows XP:

cabextract wmp11-windowsxp-x64-enu.exe -d WMP11-x64/ ; cd WMP11-x64 ;
WINEPREFIX=~/.steam/steam/steamapps/compatdata/339340/pfx/ winetricks winxp ; WINEPREFIX=~/.steam/steam/steamapps/compatdata/339340/pfx/ ~/.steam/steam/steamapps/common/Proton\ 4.11/dist/bin/wine wmfdist11-64.exe ;

This will install just enough for the videos to work. The first time the installer crashed but the second time it installed fine. 

I used d9vk and LAA but there doesn't appear to be much of a difference and may not be necessary.
